---
import Section from './Section.astro';
import SectionHeader from './SectionHeader.astro';
---

<Section>

  <SectionHeader
    eyebrow="Tips"
    title="Tips for Best Results"
    maxWidth="lg"
  />

  <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl">

    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-300">

      <li>
        • Always keep the same Master Reference Portrait throughout the entire workflow.
      </li>

      <li>
        • Never replace your Master References after creating additional angles.
      </li>

      <li>
        • Regenerate inconsistent images instead of editing them manually.
      </li>

      <li>
        • Save every reference image at the highest available resolution.
      </li>

      <li>
        • Use the final Character Reference Sheet whenever your AI image or video model supports image references.
      </li>

      <li>
        • Attach the Character Reference Sheet together with any scene-specific references (such as new clothing, props, environments, or poses) to maximize character consistency.
      </li>

      <li>
        • If your character's appearance changes during the story (such as new clothing, damaged clothing, armor changes, hairstyles, injuries, scars, dirt, blood, or other permanent visual changes), create an updated Character Reference Sheet that reflects the new look. This helps maintain consistency throughout the rest of the production.
      </li>

    </ul>

  </div>

</Section>